title: Flyleaf - Rolling Stone Originals (2006 live acoustic set)
description:
I searched in vain for this all over the net, and eventually I had to put a few hours into making it myself, taking streaming RealPlayer embedded videos and making worthwhile audio out of them, minus all the pre-video junk, etc. Why is Real still around anyway? So I figured why not share it.

It's a fantastic four-song set with Lacey on raw vocals and Sameer on an acoustic guitar. That's it. Very stripped back, very nice to listen to if you dig that kind of thing, which I do.

The songs are 192kb .m4a files, ready to play in your favorite player, importable to iTunes, and feature embedded cover art with full proper ID tags.

Track List:

* Fully Alive (2:33)
* Cassie (2:59)
* I'm So Sick (3:02)
* Sorrow (2:53)


IF YOU ENJOY THIS SMALL SET, PLEASE SUPPORT THE ARTIST.

I've played their song on Rock Band, but it wasn't until after listening to these songs, I went ahead and put the order in on Amazon to support the band: http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B000W7Y1M4 -- Hooray 2-day free shipping with Prime!
